wardens of everyday parish activities. They reveal the differences between parishes within a single diocese that cannot be attributed to regional variation. By using these records show to the range and diversity of late medieval parish life, and a Christianity vibrant enough to accommodate differences in status, wealth, gender, and local priorities, French refines our understanding of lay attitudes toward Christianity in the two centuries before the Reformation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aHISTORYvMedieval. 0aParisheszEnglandxHistoryvMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 0aParisheszEnglandxHistoryyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 4aReligious Studies. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aEuropean History.  aHistory.  aMedieval and Renaissance Studies.  aReligion.  aReligious Studies.  aWorld History.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package Complete Collectionz978311041345808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package World Historyz978311041347208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311045954840uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978081220195640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780812201956423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780812201956/original  a978-3-11-041345-8  Penn Press eBook Package Complete Collection  a978-3-11-041347-2  Penn Press eBook Package World History  a978-3-11-045954-8  University of Pennsylvania Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK